results.name: Number of partitions of n into 5 distinct nonzero squares.
link: David A. Corneth, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..9999
Index entries for sequences related to sums of squares
formula: a(n) = [x^n y^5] Product_{k>=1} (1 + y*x^(k^2)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 22 2019
maple: A025444aux := proc(n,m,nmax) local a,m,upn,lv ; if m = 1 then if issqr(n) and nmax^2 >= n and n >= 1 then return 1; else return 0; end if; else a := 0 ; for upn from 1 to nmax do lv := n-upn^2 ; if lv <0 then break; end if; a := a + procname(lv,m-1,upn-1) ; end do: return a; end if; end proc:
results.author: _David W. Wilson_
